  "prompt": "What is the best Android app for listening to and downloading English songs with lyrics?",
  "response": "There are several excellent Android apps for listening to and downloading English songs with lyrics. Here are a few of the best options:\n\n1. **Spotify**: While primarily a streaming service, Spotify allows users to listen to a vast library of songs. It has a feature that displays lyrics in real-time for many songs, and you can create and download playlists for offline listening with a premium subscription.\n\n2. **Apple Music**: Similar to Spotify, Apple Music offers a large catalog of songs, many of which include lyrics. You can download songs for offline listening if you subscribe.\n\n3. **SoundCloud**: This platform features a wide variety of music, including tracks from independent artists. Some songs come with lyrics, and while not all can be downloaded, many artists allow their tracks to be saved for offline listening.\n\n4. **Musixmatch**: This app focuses on lyrics and integrates with music streaming services like Spotify and Apple Music, allowing you to see lyrics while listening to your songs. It also offers a feature to search for songs and display lyrics.\n\n5. **YouTube Music**: YouTube Music allows you to stream a vast library of songs and watch music videos. The app often displays lyrics, and with a premium subscription, you can download music for offline listening.\n\n6. **Deezer**: Another popular music streaming service, Deezer provides access to a broad music library, and many songs come with lyrics. You can download tracks for offline listening with a premium subscription.\n\n**Note**: When downloading music, consider copyright laws and ensure that the app complies with legal requirements. Many of these services operate on a subscription model for full access, including offline downloads.",
